The paper deals with the problem of Vision-And-Language Navigation (VLN), which involves interpreting natural language instructions to navigate through a visual environment. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian state tracking and end-to-end differentiable Bayes filter also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and inference, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
